+/-0.14.\nIf this emission from U is due to dust, its opacity exponent b=a-2 would be\nabout 0.5, indicative of particle sizes that are larger than those of the\ninterstellar medium, where b(ISM)~2), but comparable to those found in\ncircumstellar discs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Apr 2019 13:02:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-08"}
